wiki.summary: "Shout Out to My Ex" is a song by British girl group Little Mix. It was released on 16 October 2016 through Syco Music as the lead single from their fourth studio album Glory Days. The song was co-written by the four group members and is about getting over an ex. It entered at the top of the UK Singles Chart, becoming the band's fourth chart-topping single, and spent three weeks at number one, becoming their second-longest charting number-one single there, behind "Black Magic". Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Shout Out to My Ex" is a song by British girl group Little Mix. It was released on 16 October 2016 through Syco Music as the lead single from their fourth studio album Glory Days. The song was co-written by the four group members and is about getting over an ex. It entered at the top of the UK Singles Chart, becoming the band's fourth chart-topping single, and spent three weeks at number one, becoming their second-longest charting number-one single there, behind "Black Magic". It was certified triple platinum in 2018, and as of 2021, it is the group's best-selling single, and the second-best selling single by a girl group in the UK. Read more on Last.fm.
